Venus Climate Could Provide a Perspective of Earth's Future
Scientists found yesterday that Venus was once a place for pleasant living conditions.
Data from a European orbiting spacecraft suggests that this planet is much more likely to be considered a whimsical twin of the Earth than previously thought.
Venus is the nearest planet to Earth.
The two planets are almost the same in size and orbit, although Venus is slightly closer to the Sun.
According to what scientists know today, billions of years ago, Venus may have had very similar living conditions and habitable conditions.
However, due to the extremely high carbon dioxide greenhouse effect, atmospheric erosion caused by solar radiation, and the planet's lower rotational velocity, Venus has entered a radically different trajectory.
